<p><b>What is the definition of educational technology 2?</b> Educational Technology is the field of study that investigates the process of analyzing, designing, developing, implementing, and evaluating the instructional environment, learning materials, learners, and the learning process in order to improve teaching and learning.</p>
<p><b>What is the main objective in educational technology 2?</b> The main objective in Educational Technology2 is to integrate various technological tools and resources into the educational process. This means incorporating technology seamlessly into teaching and learning activities to enhance student engagement, facilitate personalized learning, and improve educational outcomes.</p>
<p><b>What are the reasons behind multi channel learning in educational technology?</b> Multi-channel learning is based on the idea that the more you use a learning channel, the greater the chances of successful learning and transferring what you learn to situations we face in our daily lives. The learning channels are employed in a mutually reinforcing way.</p>
<p><b>What is the scholarly definition of educational technology?</b> Definition. The Association for Educational Communications and Technology (AECT) has defined educational technology as "the study and ethical practice of facilitating learning and improving performance by creating, using and managing appropriate technological processes and resources".</p>
<p><b>What is the concept of information technology 2?</b> It defines ICT as the use of electronic devices and software to store, process, transmit and retrieve information. Information and communication are defined, and examples of how technology aids communication and spreads information are provided.</p>
<p><b>What are the two components of educational technology?</b> It has hardware as well as software components. The former denotes technology in education and the latter technology of education. The software component makes hardware function properly and software components are redundant without appropriate hardware.</p>
<p><b>What are the characteristics of educational technology?</b> Characteristics of Educational Technology It is based on the application of the scientific knowledge. It is helpful in making the teaching process objective, easy, clear, interesting and scientific. It is a continuous dynamic technology. It is an important medium of communication.</p>
