<p><b>Why is multimedia technology important in teaching?</b> The use of video, audio, graphics, and animations can help to break up text-heavy content and can make learning more interesting and memorable when employees need to retain important information. Multimedia also ensures learning is accessible to a diverse range of learners.</p>
<p><b>Which best defines educational technology?</b> One important definition of educational technology focuses on “the technological tools and media that assist in the communication of knowledge, and its development and exchange.”</p>
<p><b>What is educational technology also known as?</b> Educational Technology (also known as edtech) is the combination of information technology (hardware, software, data, and infrastructure) with sound teaching and learning practices.</p>
